                    <msContents>
                        <summary>An anthology of Turkish lyrical poetry</summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_Or_399-item1" n="1">
                            <title key="work_23387">An anthology of Turkish lyrical poetry</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota"> اگر دلرس اولاسن سعادت ايلينه شاه الخ ... ا ...
                                ت ... ج ... ح ... د ... ذ ... ا ... ر ... دیوان غزلیات
                                شعرا</incipit>
                            <note>NOTE: This record has been automatically generated with minimal
                                modification from the corresponding entry in a printed catalogue. It
                                may contain errors. Please, consult the References section below for
                                more information.</note>
                            <note>A very defective anthology of Turkish lyrical poetry, containing
                                ḳaṣīdes, ġazels, tercīʿbands and other kinds of poetical
                                composition, but, owing to numerous lacunas, the arrangement is not
                                very clear. Ff. 1-9 are without any systematic order, beginning with
                                a murabbaʿ thus: اگر دلرس اولاسن سعادت ايلينه شاه الخ. After fol. 9
                                a large lacuna; on ff. 10-22 the poems are arranged in alphabetical
                                order, beginning in the middle of a ġazel, rhyming in ا, and
                                breaking off in a ḳaṣīde, rhyming in ت; after fol. 22 another
                                lacuna; on ff. 23-25 the alphabetical order is continued, from the
                                middle of a poem in ج to one in ح; after fol. 25 a third lacuna; on
                                ff. 26-29 continuation of the alphabetical system, comprising
                                letters د and beginning of ذ; after fol. 29 a fourth lacuna; ff. 30
                                and 31 contain poems rhyming in ا again; after fol. 31 a fifth
                                lacuna; ff. 32-35 alphabetical poems, beginning in the middle of a
                                poem, rhyming in ر and going to the end of the letter 33. The poets
                                represented are the same that have occurred in the preceding
                                collections, especially in Nos. 2150-2153, chiefly writers of the
                                time of Süleymān I and Selīm II, for instance, Bihiştī, Ḥayretī,
                                Ẕātī, etc.; Nesīmī too is met with occasionally. The title given to
                                this collection at the top of fol. 1b and at the end, دیوان غزلیات
                                شعرا, is not quite correct, as only a limited number of poems found
                                here are ġazels.</note>
